<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with at least one sign-and-direction-labeled climate feedback diagram applied to YOUR Brief's challenge.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can define tipping point, apply sign-and-direction reasoning to a climate feedback loop, and defend a position on whether tipping-point uncertainty should change my Brief's Recommendations.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Diagram one feedback for your Brief (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick the climate feedback most relevant to your adaptation challenge (e.g., urban heat island → AC demand → emissions → more warming; sea-level rise → coastal-aquifer salination → less freshwater → ...). Diagram it with sign-and-direction. Add to your Brief's Background section.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Contrast two feedbacks (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Diagram one positive (amplifying) and one negative (dampening) feedback for your challenge. Then write 3-4 sentences: what does the existence of BOTH mean for your Brief's Recommendations? Should you assume the system self-corrects, or that it runs away?</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Climate Modeler on tipping-point uncertainty (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open the <a href="/ai-partners/climate-modeler/">Climate Modeler</a>. Ask: "what's the current confidence level on [your relevant tipping point]?" Push it on uncertainty ranges. Then translate the answer into a Brief decision: how does the uncertainty shape your Recommendations?</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Sign-and-direction peer-help (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If sign-and-direction notation is fuzzy (it's a Unit 1 skill that's been quiet for a while), come to the peer-help table. Pair with a student who's solid. Use the Systems Diagrammer page as the reference.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

